description: Loki vs. Thor and Asgard – with the fate of all at stake! Ragnarök and the end of everything! Utter and total destruction is the inescapable destiny predicted for Asgard, incited by the destructive tendencies of the god of trickery. Loki has already set Ragnarök in motion, and now, if the end of the nine worlds is to be averted, Loki MUST be stopped. But how can even the gods escape the fates foretold in their stories?
name: The Trials of Loki Part 4: The Crooked Path

description: Ethaan, one of the five Angels of the dreaded caste of the Architects, seeks the help of Hellspawn Al Simmons to restore one of their oldest and most secret of weapons, the Horsaak-El. This living trap hidden in the dark alleyways of the Big Apple kept for centuries the souls of the damned, preventing them from joining the armies of Hell. But lately, the Horsaak-El has started to prey on innocent humans to quench its unbounded thirst for souls. Only a soul already marked with the seal of Hell can enter the trap to stop it. This is at least what Ethaan tells Spawn whom she wants to use as a Trojan horse to enter and destroy the mad creature. To make sure Spawn won't thwart her plan, Ethaan managed to attract one of Al Simmons' closest relatives in the heart of the Horsaak-El: his own brother Marc Simmons.
name: Architects of Fear

description: John Carter finally arrives on Mars. A pack of bloodthirsty green Martians led by the fearsome Tars Tarkas shows up to welcome him. Tars and Carter might become great friends and allies -- if they don't kill each other first! Carter find that Mars's weaker gravity imparts his earthly muscles with superhuman strength.
name: A Tale of Two Planets, Part 5

description: This April Fools Day it's Reggie's Revenge! The King of Pranks will be pranked when four brand new teams of writers and artists take on Reggie and the gang! Comic book legends join forces with Sabrina the Teenage Witch and Sonic the Hedgehog superstar comic writers for foolishly good fun!
name: The April Fool; Noon Too Soon!; Fool Me Once, Shame On Reggie!; King of Fools

description: There's a new cat lady in town, and her name is Lisa Simpson! Hoping to pad her college-bound resume with community service, Lisa lends a helping hand to Eleanor Abernathy (aka The Cat Lady) only to find that the feline-friendly female has gone missing. Soon, Lisa becomes responsible for the care and well-being of the wacky woman's whole kit and kaboodle of kitty cats...
name: Nobody's Purrfect

description: Another big 84-page, all-new issue is now available! Within it’s pages you’ll learn strange new facts relating to Synn’s ever-increasing loss of control, and what the FF may have to do about it, in a story titled “Illusions In G-Major” (guest-starring PARAGON), with script & art by Mark & Stephanie Heike. Then, learn what CAT-MAN and KITTEN did for their anniversary celebration when the US Government WOULDN’T let them use the Time Triangle to go back to 1947 in “Kitten’s Biggest Adventure”, by Rock Baker & Jeff Austin. Next, it’s a previously-untold wartime exploit starring YANKEE GIRL (guest-featuring LADY FAIRPLAY and a NEW heroine, FREEDOM GALE), “The Menace of Baroness Von Schreck”!! See why the death of Hitler might NOT have ended the Axis menace in WWII- if not for YG and friends. Plotted & layed out byGianluca Ceritelli, Scripted by Eric Johnson, with finished art by Jeff Austin. Then, the latest installment in the ongoing saga of the time-tossed adventuress STORMY TEMPEST, as an old friend from the future returns as a menace in our present in a story written by Len Strazewski, and illustrated by Scott Larson. Scott’s been penciling ST for a few issues now; this go-around he INKS his own art, as well. And, in the Gargantarama- The Comic Book flip-book half of the issue, DINOSAUR GIRL stars in a double-length WWII blockbuster, “The Last Giantess”, which introduces a “new” retro all-girl team The War Birds!! Written & drawn by Rock Baker, with ink finishes by Jeff Austin. ROWENA’S naive cousin is in the spotlight this go-around, as the Gentle Giantess must sort out GTS high jinx gone wrong in “Sera’s Day Out”, written by Eric Lindberg, with art by Rock Baker & Jeff Austin. Finally, MARLA ALLISON (a.k.a. HUMONGA ) returns in “Making A Big Scene” as a villainess’ tampering changes the script in Marla’s latest giant-woman movie, with GARGANTA herself teleported onto the set for a battle royal in front of the cameras. Written by Eric Johnson, with art by the team of Baker and Austin. Without a single reprint in sight, FF #155 is STILL the best value in comics, even at $9.95. 84 all-new, never-before-seen pages in black & white, with full color covers. Standard comic book size, saddle-stitched. Printed in 2011
name: How can the FemForce fight a menace they can't see? (Gargantarama #18 flip book)

description: It’s hard to tell who the heroes and villains are in Gantz these days. Some members of the alien-hunting team are trying to kill protagonist Kei’s girlfriend, and it’s possible he might not be able to stop them! Plus, Kei finds out about a very powerful secret related to his achieving the one--hundred--point goal.
name: Volume 16

description:
Gantz is getting absolutely intense! Our protagonist, the eternally awkward otaku boy named Kei, has hunted a bevy of odd and dangerous aliens living in Japan. The Onion Alien was strange enough, but then there were the dinosaur aliens and eventually some vampires who might not be aliens at all.

Gantz moves along at a furious pace, drowning readers in blood and violence, but then holds back for a few tender (and sometimes excessively sexy) moments here and there. It's a crazy ride so far, a guilty pleasure for many readers. See whom Kei is told to hunt next! It will certainly be a surprise.
name: Volume 15

description:
A gang of vampire guys . . . who can grow samurai swords from their very flesh! Once again, Hiroya Oku is pushing the envelope with his crazy manga Gantz!

And to add to it, these vampire yakuza guys might not even be aliens! This isn't a mission. These guys seem to know who is working for Gantz, and are coming after them. On the streets where they work and live. In the daylight. All of a sudden the wall between everyday humanity and Gantz's nighttime, extradimensional hunts is crumbling. What will Kei and the others do? Can they regenerate when they're injured outside of a mission? Find out!
name: Volume 14

description:
Dinosaurs. Seriously, can the frantic world of Gantz get any more scary? How about a giant doughboy with crazy fangs and a strange outie bellybutton? Yeah, it's not just scary; it's a very strange world for Kei!. At least this time the Gantz crew have a new weapon! It's an awesome state-of-the-art uni-motorcycle thing! And one of the characters uses a massive space samurai sword. It's Gantz!

Chapter Titles

  • 0143 - Brave Papa
  • 0144 - Howl
  • 0145 - Cannibalism
  • 0146 - Lust For Life
  • 0147 - The Odd Couple
  • 0148 - Crash
  • 0149 - Encouragement
  • 0150 - Leader
  • 0151 - Simultaneous Killings
  • 0152 - Unavoidable
  • 0153 - Decoy
  • 0154 - Feelings
name: Volume 13

description: Vampirella's pursuit of Dracula has revealed a cult of vampires, worshippers of an ancient evil, one so vast and terrible that even the Lord of the Vampires respects -- and perhaps fears -- it. As the world stands between eternal chaos and an endless army of blood-drinking horrors, Vampirella, plagued with nightmare visions of her past and of possible future, may finally have met her match.
name: Crown of Worms, Part 4
Mme Atomos Jette Un Froid part 2
Mme Atomos Cherche la Petite Bete
Mme Atomos Cherche la Petite Bete part 2

description:
The Dark X-Men are here! Norman Osborn has assembled his own mutant team, and they’re being led by Emma Frost and the Sub-Mariner! Can the X-Men survive when all the odds are against them? Cyclops has a plan...!

Includes material reprinted from Dark Avengers #7-8 and Uncanny X-Men #514.
name: The Dark X-Men!
Cip & Ciop e la grande vecchio

description:
Space Doubles' - a a retro-double feature showcasing some of the hottest/upcoming talent in comics - is presented in flip-format with each half of the book telling an original sci-fi tale ranging from alien invasions to space flight to just about everything in between. This issue features 'Project Obeah' by Leah Moore and John Reppion (Albion and Witchblade) and 'Red Rain' by Mike Raicht (Deadworld: Frozen Over and Marvel's MAX Zombie). Moore's tale is set against the backdrop of a blackened planet and focuses on the scientists attempting to colonize it, while in Raicht's story something large enough to be seen by the eye has landed on the moon, and it's up to a team of seven to investigate. Special Flip-Over Cover!

Issue One of Space Doubles was an outstanding triumph of concept and execution. For those that crave a little classic, a little retro to their diet of science/horror fiction were in for a treat. The ethos of the series was to take two stories in the mold described above and give new comic-book creators a chance to spread their wings.

Red Rain.

You lead with your strongest stuff and Red Rain is like some from the original classic science fiction short story writers mixed in with the visual style of 1950's B monster-movie shtick.

When an object big enough to be seen from earth strikes the moon a cloud of red mist blooms on the surface. Mankind assembles a team of the best and brightest to go and investigate and, in typically withering comment on consumerism, action figures are selling like hotcake of the crew even before the mission takes off.

Landing on the moon with a drop-ship the crew find and ocean forming on the surface and the mist terra-forming the atmosphere with breathable oxygen now present. Moments later hulking fish-men with breathing masks and head mounted guns emerge from the waters. The humans draw weapons on the creatures who fire first with energy beams, killing with single shots, the aliens surround the drop-ship and concentrated fire destroys it moments after an SOS is made to the Orbiter.

One female crew member is dragged alive beneath the sea, screaming long after she disappears from view. Surrounded, the remaining two crew members await their fate..... when the orbiter ship flies in strafing the area and rescuing the survivors. As the craft limps home the crew look on as another red-mist craft smashes into the earth.

Project : Obeah

In a mining operation on a distant planet a lizard like creature is found in the samples. Thought to be fossilized the creature soon proves to be very much alive and its bite sets off a zombie infection that rips through the colony.

Pickles from Pluto.

The Pickles perform single page shorts at the end of each issue as they travel the galaxy in their hamburger shaped spaceship.
name: Red Rain; Project Obeah; Red Rain

description:
A retro-double feature showcasing some of the hottest upcoming talents in comics, Space Doubles is presented in a flip-format with each half of the book telling an original sci-fi tale! Justin Robinson's 'Sympathizers' questions humanity on an Earth populated with aliens and robots, while Jason Hall's 'A Saucerful of Secretes' takes readers to a futuristic Earth where the internet allows everyone to be an entertainer and poor ratings equal death!

Saucerful of Secrets

Right from the off we are graced with the stunningly conceived art work that typifies this comic-book anthology series. Looking like something a pulp comic from the 40's and a GoldFrapp video the bold space adventure woman stands with over the top ray gun before her lemon-juicer with deco lines space rocket.

The tale behind it is not a bad one.. somewhat Gattica/Brazil-esque tale of futurist bureaucracy is somewhat flat that some how gets muted when it has little to do with such inspiring cover art (especially when every other stories cover art is story appropriate)

Sympathizers.

A bizarrely noir-ish tale of fish-men and robot invasion.
name: Saucerful of Secrets; Sympathizers

description:
A 1-shot story based on the character Roadkill. 
Unique in the sense that the title character first appeared in Marvel comics and the issue was published outside of Marvel
Celebrating 60 years of Dennis the Menace.

name: Topolino e la chioma di Berenice

volume.name: Shadowmen 2: Heroes and Villains of French Comics

name: Muzo et la Machine à Laver
Placid, Muzo et la Machine à Sous
Placid et Muzo Vont au Bal Masqué

description: Merlin іѕ a ten-volume series οf graphic novels аbουt thе wizard οf Arthurian legend originally published іn French аnԁ Dutch іn 2001 bу European publishers Talent аnԁ Soleil. Thе series wаѕ re-issued іn 2010 bу European publisher Silvester.
name: The Fury Of Ahes

description:
When circus acrobat Boston Brand died, a mysterious supernatural being called Rama Kushna gave him the ability to enter and possess the bodies of the living. Obsessed with exacting revenge against the man that killed him, Deadman began an afterlife of vengeance but soon turned his paranormal abilities towards more heroic endeavors. DEADMAN COLLECTION is an intriguing look into the beginning of Deadman's quest for his killer as he struggles to understand and accept his new existence.  
 
 Collects: Aquaman [backup] #50-52, Strange Adventures #205-216, Challengers of the Unkown #74 and The Brave and the Bold #79, 86 and 104.
name: Deadman Collection

description: First in a trilogy, Book One: Damsels explores the lives of the partners/side-kicks of the major heroes in the Action Bunny Universe in short, introductory stories, revealing their worlds from their point of view. Nudity involved-mature reading.

person_credits.name: Dupe
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover, production

description: The re-introduction of the 'Knight-Terror' and the legacy revealed through generations, starting from the jungles of Africa, ending in the concrete jungle of a city called 'Prominence'. The short stories jump from father to son as we see how Knightmare stalks the criminal underbelly, striking fear from the shadows.
name: Knightshades

description:
Wraparound cover: Henry Flint (Shakara)

  • Judge Dredd - Served Cold (part 8 - final part) (Al Ewing - John Higgins)
  • Shakara - Avenger (part 12) (Robbie Morrison - Henry Flint)
  • Flesh - Texas (part 2) (Pat Mills - James McKay)
  • Future Shocks - The Last James Drillard (T.C.Eglington - Joel Carpenter)
  • Kingdom - His Master's Voice (part 12 - final part) (Dan Abnett - Richard Elson)

name: Prog 1725

description: A new volume collecting BLUE BEETLE #7-12! Jaime discovers the secret of his Blue Beetle armor and hits the road looking for answers from the Scarab's original owner.
name: Road Trip

description:
Hinohara is surprised to learn that Kotoha no longer believes he’s Arata of the Hime clan. Meanwhile, a group within the Twelve Shinsho sets in motion a diabolical plan to eliminate Hinohara!

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 38: Thank You
  • Chapter 39: Omen
  • Chapter 40: Who Are You?
  • Chapter 41: Starting Over
  • Chapter 42: Change
  • Chapter 43: The Inner Six Sho
  • Chapter 44: Bad Premonition
  • Chapter 45: Resonance
  • Chapter 46: The Chosen One
  • Chapter 47: Orochi
name: Vol. 5

description: All right, listen up. Today I want to talk about "expectations"!
name: Vol. 8

description: Mihai enters the stage just in time to save Badou from starring in his own death scene, but now the two of them are a captive audience to Beltheim’s display of his lethal skills. As bad as things are in the Above though, they’re even worse in the Below: under Giovanni’s command, the dog soldiers have started their final assault against the underground city. As the streets around them burn, Heine and Giovanni become locked in a savage fight to settle their rivalry once and for all.
name: Volume 5

description: By now Hayate's nigh-total awesomeness is a matter of public record. But how did he come to master the twin disciplines of housekeeping and martial arts? In the ﬂashback to end all ﬂashbacks, we journey back to Hayate's hapless childhood and his cryptic encounter with the girl who would change his life forever. Be forewarned--the drama tag will be pulled.
name: Vol. 17

description: Mikito and Kugai encounter a powerful being called Suguri, who has been spreading ogre seeds and killing monsters wherever he goes. He wants to destroy Mikito, but he must battle Kugai and a special hunter named Gogyo first. Will Mikito unleash his awesome ogre powers?
name: Vol. 3

description: Ageha, a young shinigami girl with a serious grudge against the evil Damashigami Company, searches for her missing sister with Rinne’s help. Ageha is head over heels for Rinne, but he’s got Sakura Mamiya on his mind. And how does Sakura feel about this odd ghost-busting love triangle?
name: Vol. 5

description: They've made it past getting on each other’s nerves, and Hazuki and Nanoha are now friends. But the more time he spends with Nanoha, the more Hazuki discovers a new side to himself--could this lead to love?! Too bad Nanoha doesn't have a clue. It's beyond her to figure out why Hazuki is suddenly becoming distant and can't seem to look her in the eye anymore... Will Nanoha's little internal monster reappear to save the day?
name: Vol. 2

description:
Ginji Ishikawa despises anything related to the occult. The hatred stems from the visions of his dead brother's ghost that haunts him nightly. When an incident at a haunted mansion lands him in hot water, only the assistance of a child named Ageha gets him out of trouble. However, Ageha suggests Ginji repay the debt by serving the very last line of work he ever wanted: ghost busting!

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 1: All the Ghosts In This World
  • Chapter 2: Money Is Everything In the World
  • Chapter 3: Not A Ghost
  • Chapter 4: Even What You Can See
  • Chapter 5: Need You
  • Chapter 6: Practically An Accident
  • Chapter 7: Just Like A Ghost
  • Chapter 8: Gliding Through Time
  • Chapter 9: A Prideful Ghost
name: Vol. 1

description: First in a trilogy, Action Bunny Comix- Book One: Damsels, is a collection of short  stories told in the perspectives of the partner/side-kicks of the leading heroes of the Action Bunny Universe, with a slightly humorous slant. nudity involved, adult content.

K2 doesn’t understand why he can’t sleep in Mona’s bed. When no one wants to give him The Talk he starts asking strangers! Will his naïvety get him seduced by an older woman?! Meanwhile, Rina is dealing with the confusion of her own growing feelings of love. Distracted by their personal drama, will the Koigusa family miss the fact that Helmet is slowly moving forward with his global strategy to defeat the Intelligence...?
name: Vol. 4

description: Kokaku must fight to save a friend and his ideals against his biggest foe, his archnemesis Shikki! It seems Kokaku's desire not to kill is more fiery than the hottest pepper in town, but everyone is out to break Kokaku's will as he protects Shinnosuke, Kôki's school and the local dojos. Will the hero prevail after all? Plus, a bonus manga about the the ninja who started it all!
name: Vol. 4

description: Their relationship is gradually moving to a new level, but will Misaki ever be able to admit to Usui that she's happy about it? Meanwhile, Hinata's not about to give up on his pursuit. But when Usui is unintentionally invited to dinner at Misaki's house and given the chance to work his charming magic on her family, even Hinata may finally have to admit that he's losing the battle for Misaki's heart. Then, with the school election on the horizon, a new challenge appears when the first year students decide that they want to overthrow Demon President Misaki--and they think hapless Kanou is the right man for the job!
name: Vol. 8

description: It is near the end of the Meiji Era in Japan, Nanao Kaga defies her father’s opposition and attends a music academy in Tokyo, in search for “Prince of Harmony”, the man of her dreams. Meanwhile, Takenomaru Sagami is a violinist prodigy on a quest--he looks for Tear of Maria as part of the contract with the Great Angel. When Nanao meets Takenomaru, will Nanao’s dream finally come true?
name: Vol. 1

description: "Ghost Academy" chronicles the early years of six StarCraft characters all destined for greatness - and tragedy! Five teenaged fourth-class Terrans (Nova, Tosh, Aal, Kath, and Lio) are rough-around-the-edges Ghost cadets in training - and they are forced to deal with everyday teen issues such as crushes, physical and emotional pain, addiction to drugs, and their own budding telepathic abilities.
name: Vol. 3

description: Mafuyu and Tomo continue their normal school life while fighting off qwasers who continue to search for the Theotokos of Sary Su. Meanwhile, a new mysterious girl from Russia has arrived in Japan, but is she an ally or an enemy? Now the only two available options to save Tomo from the holy nail embedded into her chest are to defeat the Golden Qwaser or depend on the miraculous power of the icon that everyone is searching for!
name: Vol. 2

description: Tomo is left with a bad leg injury after diving into the stormy sea to retrieve her precious agate and the school is buzzing with gossip after Riku rescues her. Between beach crafts and planning Tento's birthday party, Tomo tries to reconcile with Michiru, who is upset that Riku told Tomo about his sister's death. Can Tomo find the troubled girl a place to fit in at school? All seems lost when Riku signs Tento and Tomo up for a spot at a local flea market. Are Tento's beach creations really up to the test?
name: Vol. 2

description: When yakuza gangster, Kazuma, falls wounded at the doorstep of a young tea ceremony master named Yukihiro, he's sure he'll be reported and put behind bars at once. But he's shocked when Yukihiro shows him only the utmost in kindness and trust. Despite coming from two completely different backgrounds, the two men find out they're more alike than they thought. Infused with angst and drama, this story of tea leaves and lovers will seep it way into your heart.
name: Vol. 1

description: After a traumatic childhood experience at an amusement park, Sata Senda became the local poster-boy for compulsive cleanliness. Equipped with anti-bacterial spray, an array of masks and kind of scary protective clothing, he's not exactly easy to get close to, and he's fine with that...at least until Anna Aiuchi, the class cutie, goes out of her way to break through his personal bubble! Suddenly Senda's life begins to change, invaded by one messy personality after another. Can the cleansing power of friendship finally overcome Sata's quirks? Find out in the first volume of this hilarious new comedy!
name: Vol. 1

description: Ragnok Bloodreaver leads his fel orc and nether dragon army to the Outland Gates. Tyri reveals to Zzeraku the true origins of the nether dragons, in that they were the offspring of Deathwing, the monstrous dragon aspect. Jorad and Valwar see Ragnok approaching and go warn the alliance of the pending attack. A great battle ensues, with Tyri, Valoku and Zaeraku joining the fight. Jorad killes Ragnok, and nether dragons travel through the portal to Northrend. But after bathing in the energies of the Nexus, Zzeraku gives the order for the nether dragons to attack the blue dragons. Malygos awakens and absorbs the nether dragons. Tyri and Jorad return to Outland; Tyri finds another clutch of nether eggs and decides to stay in Outland to protect them.
name: Nexus Point

description: In this adorable volume of Happy Café... Sakura and Jiro become friends at their preschool. But Jiro is weak and has a hard time staying alert. What kind words does Uru have for her little friend? And when Uru’s class decides to hold a café-themed event at the school festival, Boss sends Uru and Shindo out on a cake hunt...alone together! Will this “date” take their relationship to the next level?
name: Vol. 6
